<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="165" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="165">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="165">Rigid and opaque body. Narrow collarette and extending to half distance from neck to ventral ganglion. Intestinal diverticula present. Grasping spine gently curved. Two rows of stout teeth arranged in comb shape. Two pairs of lateral fins completely rayed, anterior fins beginning at end of ventral ganglion. Seminal vesicles oval-shaped with opening at anterolateral edge, position of seminal vesicles well separated from caudal fin, but touching posterior fins.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="165" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="165">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="165">
This species is found in the epipelagic zone (0-200 m depth) of the Pacific and Indian Oceans (
<bibRefCitation author="Pierrot-Bults, AC" editor="Bone, Q" journalOrPublisher="Oxford Science Publications, New York" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" pagination="86 - 116" refId="B70" refString="Pierrot-Bults, AC, Nair, VR, 1991. Distribution patterns in Chaetognatha. In: Bone, Q, Kapp, H, Pierrot-Bults, AC, Eds., The Biology of the Chaetognaths. Oxford Science Publications, New York: 86 - 116" title="Distribution patterns in Chaetognatha." volumeTitle="The Biology of the Chaetognaths." year="1991">Pierrot-Bults and Nair 1991</bibRefCitation>
) and the coastal waters of the Philippines, India and Hong Kong (
<bibRefCitation author="George, PC" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the National Institute of Sciences of India" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" pagination="657 - 689" refId="B28" refString="George, PC, 1952. A systematic account of the chaetognatha of the Indian coastal waters, with observations on their seasonal fluctuations along the Malabar Coast. Proceedings of the National Institute of Sciences of India 18 (6): 657 - 689" title="A systematic account of the chaetognatha of the Indian coastal waters, with observations on their seasonal fluctuations along the Malabar Coast." volume="18" year="1952">George 1952</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ecss.2007.01.011" author="Tse, P" journalOrPublisher="Estuarine, Coastal and Shelf Science" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" pagination="290 - 298" refId="B92" refString="Tse, P, Hui, SY, Wong, CK, 2007. Species composition and seasonal abundance of Chaetognatha in the subtropical coastal waters of Hong Kong. Estuarine, Coastal and Shelf Science 73 (1-2): 290 - 298, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ecss.2007.01.011" title="Species composition and seasonal abundance of Chaetognatha in the subtropical coastal waters of Hong Kong." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ecss.2007.01.011" volume="73" year="2007">Tse et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1093/icesjms/fsn027" author="Noblezada, MMP" journalOrPublisher="ICES Journal of Marine Science" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" pagination="484 - 494" refId="B58" refString="Noblezada, MMP, Campos, WL, 2008. Spatial distribution of chaetognaths off the northern Bicol Shelf, Philippines (Pacific coast). ICES Journal of Marine Science 65 (3): 484 - 494, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1093/icesjms/fsn027" title="Spatial distribution of chaetognaths off the northern Bicol Shelf, Philippines (Pacific coast)." url="https://doi.org/10.1093/icesjms/fsn027" volume="65" year="2008">Noblezada and Campos 2008</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1093/plankt/fbs041" author="Lie, AA" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Plankton Research" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" pagination="670 - 684" refId="B44" refString="Lie, AA, Tse, P, Wong, CK, 2012. Diel vertical migration and feeding of three species of chaetognaths (Flaccisagitta enflata, Aidanosagitta delicata and Aidanosagitta neglecta) in two shallow, subtropical bays in Hong Kong. Journal of Plankton Research 34 (8): 670 - 684, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1093/plankt/fbs041" title="Diel vertical migration and feeding of three species of chaetognaths (Flaccisagitta enflata, Aidanosagitta delicata and Aidanosagitta neglecta) in two shallow, subtropical bays in Hong Kong." url="https://doi.org/10.1093/plankt/fbs041" volume="34" year="2012">Lie et al. 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="165" type="ecology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="165">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="165">
A mature specimen has been reported to be 8 mm is size (
<bibRefCitation author="Alvarino, A" journalOrPublisher="University of California, Scripps Institution of Oceanography" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" refId="B4" refString="Alvarino, A, 1967. The Chaetognatha of the NAGA Expedition (1959-1961): In the South China Sea and the Gulf of Thailand (Vol. 4). University of California, Scripps Institution of Oceanography" title="The Chaetognatha of the NAGA Expedition (1959 - 1961): In the South China Sea and the Gulf of Thailand (Vol. 4)." year="1967">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Alvariño">Alvarino</normalizedToken>
1967
</bibRefCitation>
). This species shows a diurnal vertical migration in the summer off the Hong Kong coast (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1093/plankt/fbs041" author="Lie, AA" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Plankton Research" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" pagination="670 - 684" refId="B44" refString="Lie, AA, Tse, P, Wong, CK, 2012. Diel vertical migration and feeding of three species of chaetognaths (Flaccisagitta enflata, Aidanosagitta delicata and Aidanosagitta neglecta) in two shallow, subtropical bays in Hong Kong. Journal of Plankton Research 34 (8): 670 - 684, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1093/plankt/fbs041" title="Diel vertical migration and feeding of three species of chaetognaths (Flaccisagitta enflata, Aidanosagitta delicata and Aidanosagitta neglecta) in two shallow, subtropical bays in Hong Kong." url="https://doi.org/10.1093/plankt/fbs041" volume="34" year="2012">Lie et al. 2012</bibRefCitation>
). The temperature range in the sampling stations of this study was 16.40-16.41 °C and the salinity was 34.58 psu.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="165" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="165">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="165">
Only one immature individual was collected in this study. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Aida" baseAuthorityYear="1897" class="Sagittoidea" family="Sagittidae" genus="Aidanosagitta" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aidanosagitta neglecta" order=" Aphragmophora" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" phylum="Chaetognatha" rank="species" species="neglecta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">Aidanosagitta neglecta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. regularis" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" rank="species" species="regularis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">A. regularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in morphological characteristics including collarette. However, the former had much larger seminal vesicles, thus they can be easily distinguished from each other. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Aida" baseAuthorityYear="1897" class="Sagittoidea" family="Sagittidae" genus="Aidanosagitta" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aidanosagitta neglecta" order=" Aphragmophora" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" phylum="Chaetognatha" rank="species" species="neglecta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">Aidanosagitta neglecta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
collected from Korean waters was smaller than the previously reported adult specimens, but seminal vesicles were obviously swollen in an oval shape. Despite the presence of swollen seminal vesicles, the Korean specimen was considered as immature because its size was smaller than the known record of the adult (
<bibRefCitation author="Alvarino, A" journalOrPublisher="University of California, Scripps Institution of Oceanography" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" refId="B4" refString="Alvarino, A, 1967. The Chaetognatha of the NAGA Expedition (1959-1961): In the South China Sea and the Gulf of Thailand (Vol. 4). University of California, Scripps Institution of Oceanography" title="The Chaetognatha of the NAGA Expedition (1959 - 1961): In the South China Sea and the Gulf of Thailand (Vol. 4)." year="1967">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Alvariño">Alvarino</normalizedToken>
1967
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
